ring cup.","Add tomatoes and corn and cook <nobr>1 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Heat remaining olive oil in a non-stick frying pan and cook burgers for 2 minutes on each side. Halve buns, spread barbecue sauce on both sides, place onion mixture, then a burger and a slice of Emmental on base. Place top of bun on burgers, place in oven and cook for 5 minutes (200°C). Remove from oven, add some salad leaves to garnish and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Burger buns","content":["50 g water","10 g fresh yeast","50 g milk","15 g caster sugar","250 g plain flour","2 eggs","40 g butter","1 pinch fine salt","1 tbsp sesame seeds"]},{"title":"Barbecue sauce","content":["30 g shallots","1 garlic clove","15 g olive oil","1 pinch ground cayenne pepper","50 g brown sugar","125 g tomato passata","2 tbsp mustard","1 tbsp lemon juice              (optional)","1 tsp Worcestershire sauce","1 tsp cornflour (starch)"]},{"title":"Tex-mex burgers","content":["100 g onions, cut into halves","1 garlic clove","25 g olive oil","2 tsp Mexican spice mix or any other spice mix of choice","1 pinch ground cayenne pepper","150 g tomatoes, diced","50 g canned sweetcorn kernels, drained","600 g beef mince, formed into 5 burger patties","6 slices Emmental cheese or any other medium-hard cheese (e.g. cheddar, gouda)","30 g salad leaves, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r129361","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-tOAziynM1Pg\/XZQG3q4cTcI\/AAAAAAAAcCw\/A-pVIxizWgkIOhowHl5wHhOHI_Y6cvSkgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ZAzCjAUy01TMmhUa.png","title":"Tex-mex burger","publishedAt":"2017-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"60 g","fat":"38 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"56 g","calories":"3377 kJ \/ 808 kcal"},"usefulItems":"tea towel, baking tray, baking paper, pastry brush, large bowl, bowl, non-stick frying pan, oven","basicInfo":["medium","40m","4h 25m","5 pieces"]}